son Latham |location=Oxford and New York |publisher=Oxford University Press |ISBN=0-19-866212-2 |ref=harv }}\n*{{cite book |last=Latham |first=Alison |year=2002b |chapter=Metre |title=The Oxford Companion to Music |url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9780198662129 |url-access=registration |others=edited by Alison Latham |location=Oxford and New York |publisher=Oxford University Press |ISBN=0-19-866212-2 |ref=harv }}\n*{{cite book |last=Lee |first=C. S. |year=1985 |chapter=The Rhythmic Interpretation of Simple Musical Sequences: Towards a Perceptual Model |editor3=Robert West |editor=Peter Howell |editor2=Ian Cross |title=Musical Structure and Cognition |location=London |publisher=Academic Press |ISBN=978-0-12357170-0 |ref=harv}}\n*{{Cite book| first = Joel | last = Lester | year = 1986 | title = The Rhythms of Tonal Music | publisher = Southern Illinois University Press | location = Carbondale | isbn = 0-8093-1282-4 |ref=harv }}\n*{{cite book |last=London |first=Justin |year=2001 |chapter=Rhythm |title=The New Grove Dictionary of Music and Musicians |others=second edition, edited by [[Stanley Sadie]] and [[John Tyrrell (professor of music)|John Tyrrell]] |location=London |publisher=Macmillan Publishers |ref=harv}}\n*{{Cite book| first = Justin | last = London | year = 2004 | title = Hearing in Time: Psychological Aspects of Musical Meter |edition=first |publisher = Oxford University Press | location = Oxford | isbn = 0-19-516081-9 |ref=harv }}\n*{{Cite book| first = Justin | last = London | year = 2012 | title = Hearing in Time: Psychological Aspects of Musical Meter |edition=second|publisher = Oxford University Press | location = Oxford | isbn = 978-0-19-974437-4 |ref=harv }}\n*{{Cite book |last=MacPherson |first=Stewart |year=1930 |title=Form in Music |location=London |publisher=Joseph Williams Ltd |ref=harv }}\n*{{Cite web |author=Merriam-Webster|year=2015 |title=Measure|work=Dictionary |location=New York|url=http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/measure|ref