 - ''Chasing the Storm''\n* [[Trouble (band)|Trouble]] - ''[[The Skull (album)|The Skull]]''\n* [[Twisted Sister]] - ''[[Come Out and Play (Twisted Sister album)|Come Out and Play]]''\n* [[220 Volt (band)|220 Volt]] - ''Mind over Muscle''\n* [[Tygers of Pan Tang]] - ''[[The Wreck-Age]]''\n* [[Ralf Scheepers#Tyran' Pace|Tyran' Pace]] - ''Long Live Metal''\n* Tyrant (Ger) - ''Fight for Your Life''\n* Tyrant (US) - ''Legions of the Dead''\n* Tysondog - ''Shoot to Kill'' (EP)\n* [[Tytan (band)|Tytan]] - ''Rough Justice''\n* Tzar (Can) \u2013 ''Players of the Game''\n* [[UFO (band)|UFO]] - ''[[Misdemeanor (UFO album)|Misdemeanor]]''\n* Universe - ''Universe'' \n* Vampyr - ''Cry Out for Metal''\n* [[Vanadium (band)|Vanadium]] - ''On Streets of Danger'' (live)\n* [[Vandenberg (band)|Vandenberg]] - ''[[Alibi (Vandenberg album)|Alibi]]''\n* [[Venom (band)|Venom]] - ''[[Possessed (Venom album)|Possessed]]''\n* [[Vicious Rumors]] - ''[[Soldiers of the Night]]''\n* [[Victory (band)|Victory]] - ''Victory''\n* Vyper - ''Afraid of the Dark'' (EP)\n* [[Virgin Steele]] - ''[[Noble Savage (album)|Noble Savage]]''\n* [[Bow Wow (band)|Vow Wow]] - ''Cyclone''\n* [[Vulcain (band)|Vulcain]] - ''La dame de fer'' (EP)\n* Vulcain - ''Desperados''\n* [[W.A.S.P. (band)|W.A.S.P.]] - ''[[The Last Command (album)|The Last Command]]''\n* [[Warlock (band)|Warlock]] - '' [[Hellbound (Warlock album)|Hellbound]]''\n* [[Warrior (band)|Warrior]] - '' [[Fighting for the Earth]]\n* Warhead (Bel) - ''The Day After''\n* Warrant (Ger) - ''First Strike'' (EP)\n* Warrant (Ger) - ''The Enforcer''\n* [[Watchtower (band)|Watchtower]] - ''[[Energetic Disassembly]]''\n* [[Waysted]] - ''[[The Good the Bad the Waysted]]''\n* [[White Lion]] - ''[[Fight to Survive]]''\n* Wizard - ''Marlin, Grog, Madman & The Bomb'' \n* World War III (PA) \u2013 ''World War III''\n* [[Wrathchild]] (UK) - ''[[Trash Queens]]'' (comp)\n* [[Y&T]] - ''[[Open Fire (Y&T album)|Open Fire]]'' (live)\n* Y&T - ''[[Down for the Count (album)|Down for the Count]]''\n* [[Yngwie Malmsteen]] - ''[[Marching Out]]''\n* Zero Nine \u2013 ''White Lines''\n* [[Zoetrope (band)|Zoetrope]] - ''Amnesty''\n* [[Znowhite]] - ''[[Kick 'Em When They're Down|Kick 'Em When They're Down EP]]''\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Disbandments==\n* [[Mercyful Fate]] (reformed in [[1992 in heavy metal music|1992]])\n* [[Van Halen]] (Roth quits band)\n\n==Events==\n* [[Living Colour]] guitarist [[Vernon Reid]] cofounds the [[Black Rock Coalition]], a [[non-profit organization]] dedicated to promoting the creative freedom and works of black musicians interested in playing rock music.\n* [[Twisted Sister]]'s [[Dee Snider]] testifies at The [[Parents Music Resource Center]] Senate hearings on rock censorship at Washington D.C. on September 19, 1985.\n* [[David Lee Roth]] releases his solo debut (EP) ''[[Crazy from the Heat]]'' in January 1985. With it comes the announcement he has permanently left [[Van Halen]].\n* [[Black Sabbath]] reunites at [[Live Aid]] with [[Ozzy Osbourne]].\n* [[Led Zeppelin]] reunites at [[Live Aid]] with Phil Collins replacing deceased drummer [[John Bonham]].\n* [[Kam Lee]] leaves [[Death (metal band)|Death]] and [[Chuck Schuldiner]] becomes the vocalist.\n* [[Uriah Heep (band)|Uriah Heep]]'s former lead singer, [[David Byron]] dies on February 28, due to alcohol complications.\n* ''[[Welcome to Venice]]'' compilation is released, featuring [[Suicidal Tendencies]], [[Beowulf]], <<link:0>> and others, showing the growing crossover trend among the Venice Beach hardcore and metal scenes.\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{Timeline box|title=[[Timeline of heavy metal music|Heavy Metal Timeline]]|before=[[1984 in heavy metal music|1984]]|after=[[1986 in heavy metal music|1986]]|year='''1985'''}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Timeline of heavy metal and hard rock music}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1985 In Heavy Metal Music}}\n[[Category:1980s in heavy metal music]]\n[[Category:1985 in music|Metal]]\n", "text_old": "{{Year in music|1985}}\n{{Year nav topic5|1985|heavy metal music}}\n{{unreferenced|date=February 2015}}\nThis is a timeline documenting the events of [[Heavy Metal music|heavy metal]] in the year 1985.\n\n==Newly formed bands==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* [[Acid Reign]]\n* [[Aria (band)|Aria]]\n* [[Atrocity (band)|Atrocity]]\n* [[Carcass (band)|Carcass]]\n* [[David Lee Roth]]\n* [[Deliverance (metal band)|Deliverance]]\n* [[Dream Theater]] (under the name \"Majesty\")\n* [[Exhorder]]\n* [[Extreme (band)|Extreme]]\n* [[Extreme Noise Terror]]\n* [[Exumer\n* [[Guns N' Roses]]\n* [[Hunter (band)|Hunter]]\n* [[Jane's Addiction]]\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n{{col-2}}\n* [[King Diamond (band)|King Diamond]]\n* [[Macabre (band)|Macabre]]\n* [[Mekong Delta (band)|Mekong Delta]]\n* [[Mortal Sin (band)|Mortal Sin]]\n* [[Mr. Bungle]]\n* [[MX Machine]]\n* [[Neurosis (band)|Neurosis]]\n* [[Poltergeist (band)|Poltergeist]]\n* [[Sabbat (English band)|Sabbat]]\n* [[Sacred Reich]]\n* [[Sanctuary (band)|Sanctuary]]\n* [[Sarc\u00f3fago]]\n* [[Shadow Gallery]]\n* [[Stone (band)|Stone]]\n* [[Stormtroopers of Death]]\n* [[Tarot (band)|Tarot]] (under the name \"Purgatory\" until record deal)\n* [[Tormentor (band)|Tormentor]]\n* [[Toxik]]\n* [[Vio-lence]]\n* [[Viper (band)|Viper]]\n* [[White Zombie (band)|White Zombie]]\n\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Albums & EPs==\n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[Lee Aaron]] - ''[[Call of the Wild (Lee Aaron album)|Call of the Wild]]''\n* [[Abattoir (band)|Abattoir]] - ''Vicious Attack''\n* [[AC/DC]] - ''[[Fly on the Wall (AC/DC album)|Fly on the Wall]]''\n* [[Accept (band)|Accept]] - ''[[Metal Heart]]''\n* Acid \u2013 ''Engine Beast''\n* [[ADX (band)|ADX]] - ''Ex\u00e9cution''\n* [[Aerosmith]] - ''[[Done with Mirrors]]''\n* [[Agent Steel]] - ''[[Skeptics Apocalypse]]''\n* Agent Steel - ''[[Mad Locust Rising]]'' (EP)\n* [[Alcatrazz]] - ''[[Disturbing the Peace (album)|Disturbing the Peace]]''\n* [[Angel Witch]] - ''[[Screamin' 'n' Bleedin']]''\n* [[Anthem (band)|Anthem]] - ''Anthem''\n* Anthem - ''Ready to Ride'' (EP)\n* [[Anthrax (American band)|Anthrax]] - ''[[Armed and Dangerous (EP)|Armed and Dangerous]]'' (EP)\n* Anthrax - ''[[Spreading the Disease]]''\n* [[Anvil (band)|Anvil]] - ''[[Backwaxed]]'' (comp)\n* [[April Wine]] - ''[[Walking Through Fire]]''\n* [[Aria (band)|Aria]] - ''[[Mania Velichia]]''\n* Armed Force - ''Heavy Artillery''\n* [[Armored Saint]] - ''[[Delirious Nomad]]''\n* [[Artillery (band)|Artillery]] - ''[[Fear of Tomorrow]]''\n* Astaroth - ''The Long Loud Silence'' (EP)\n* [[Atomkraft]] - ''Future Warriors''\n* Attacker - ''Battle at Helm's Deep''\n* [[Autograph (American band)|Autograph]] - ''[[That's the Stuff]]''\n* [[Avenger (British band)|Avenger]] (UK) - ''[[Killer Elite (album)|Killer Elite]]''\n* [[Rage (German band)|Avenger]] (Ger) - ''[[Depraved to Black]]'' (EP)\n* Avenger (Ger) - ''[[Prayers of Steel]]''\n* [[Axewitch]] - ''[[Hooked on High Heels]]''\n* Axtion \u2013 ''Look Out For The Night''\n* Bad Lizard \u2013 ''Power of Destruction''\n* [[Bar\u00f3n Rojo]] - ''[[En un lugar de la marcha]]''\n* [[Bathory (band)|Bathory]] - ''[[The Return\u2026\u2026]]''\n* [[Barren Cross]] - ''Believe'' (EP)\n* Beast (Ger) - ''Like Living In A Cage''\n* Black Angels \u2013 ''Broken Spell''\n* Black Angels \u2013 ''Black and White''\n* Black Knight - ''Master of Disaster'' (EP)\n* Black Lace - ''Get It While It's Hot''\n* [[Black 'n Blue]] - ''[[Without Love (Black 'n Blue album)|Without Love]]''\n* [[Black Rose (British band)|Black Rose]] \u2013 ''Nightmare'' (EP)\n* Black Sheep - ''Trouble in the Streets''\n* Blaspheme \u2013 ''D\u00e9sir de Vampyr''\n* Blessed Death - ''Kill or Be Killed''\n* [[Satan (band)|Blind Fury]] - ''Out of Reach''\n* [[Harem Scarem|Blind Vengeance]] \u2013 ''Blind Vengeance''\n* [[Blitzkrieg (band)|Blitzkrieg]] (UK) - ''[[A Time of Changes (album)|A Time of Changes]]''\n* Blitzkrieg (US) - ''Ready for Action'' (EP)\n* Bloodlust - ''Guilty as Sin''\n* [[Blue \u00d6yster Cult]] - ''[[Club Ninja]]''\n* [[Bon Jovi]] - ''[[7800\u00b0 Fahrenheit]]''\n* [